"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084421","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2019-03-20","<p>The Chief Scientific Adviser had no meetings with my rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019. The Chief Scientific Adviser met with the Minister of State for Universities, Science, Research and Innovation on 29 January 2019.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2019-03-20T11:26:53.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084421/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084421/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084421/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2019-03-08","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many meetings he had with his Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","230034"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084422","Cabinet Office","false","2019-03-15","<p>I refer the Right Honourable Member to my answer given to Question 198752 on 7 January 2019.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2019-03-15T14:43:34.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084422/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084422/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084422/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-03-08","Cabinet Office: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many meetings he held with his Department's Chief Scientific Adviser between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","230035"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084423","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-03-12","<p>The Secretary of State had numerous meetings attended by analysts and technical specialists in the Department between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019.</p><p>Our Chief Scientific Adviser role is currently being recruited and interviews are scheduled for Thursday 28 March.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2019-03-12T15:02:06.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084423/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084423/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084423/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-03-08","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, how many meetings he held with his Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","230036"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084424","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-03-13","<p>Between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019 there have been no meetings between myself and the Ministry of Defence Chief Scientific Adviser.</p>","South Staffordshire","Gavin Williamson",,"2019-03-13T15:31:16.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084424/answer","Biography information for Gavin Williamson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084424/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084424/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-03-08","Ministry of Defence: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many meetings he held with his Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","230037"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084425","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-03-18","<p>The Chief Scientific Adviser attends meetings with Ministers on a regular basis.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2019-03-18T16:55:38.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084425/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084425/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084425/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-03-08","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many meetings he held with his Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","230038"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084426","Department for Education","false","2019-03-18","<p>My right hon. Friend, the Secretary of State for Education has not had any one-to-one meetings with the Chief Scientific Adviser between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019. However, during this time, the Chief Scientific Adviser has been present at two meetings my right hon. Friend, the Secretary of State for Education has held with officials, and regularly provides written advice.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2019-03-18T10:09:43.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084426/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084426/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084426/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-03-08","Department for Education: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many meetings he held with his Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","230039"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084427","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-03-14","<p>The Secretary of State had two bilateral meetings with Defra’s Chief Scientific Adviser between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019. The Chief Scientific Adviser also regularly attends other Secretary of State meetings on wider issues.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2019-03-14T10:32:07.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084427/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084427/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084427/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-03-08","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many meetings he held with his Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","230040"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084428","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2019-03-13","<p>Between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019, the Secretary of State met with Chris Jones, Chief Scientific Adviser at DExEU, on two occasions. It should be noted that this is a dual role for Chris Jones, and is combined with his position as the Director of Justice, Security and Migration.</p><p> </p>","Daventry","Chris Heaton-Harris",,"2019-03-13T11:14:06.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084428/answer","Biography information for Chris Heaton-Harris","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084428/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084428/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2019-03-08","Department for Exiting the European Union: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many meetings he held with his Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","230041"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084429","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-03-14","<p>FCO Minister's offices have regular meetings with the Department's Chief Scientific Adviser, and her Deputy. I most recently met with the Chief Scientific Adviser on 16 October 2018.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2019-03-14T12:00:13.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084429/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084429/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084429/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-03-08","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many meetings he held with his Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","230042"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084430","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-03-14","<p>For the period 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019, my Rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care met with the Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser (CSA) seven times, and the CSA met with other Health and Social Care ministers on 12 occasions.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2019-03-14T10:50:16.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084430/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084430/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084430/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-03-08","Department of Health and Social Care: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many meetings he held with his Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","230043"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084431","Treasury","false","2019-03-18","<p>Between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019, the Chancellor of the Exchequer met with the Chief Scientific Adviser/Director of the Enterprise and Growth Unit at HM Treasury, on five occasions.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2019-03-18T14:56:29.09Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084431/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084431/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084431/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-03-08","Treasury: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many meetings he held with his Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","230044"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084432","Home Office","false","2019-03-28","<p>Home Office Ministers have regular meetings with Ministerial colleagues and others as part of the process of policy development and delivery. The Home Secretary met Professor John Aston in September and November 2018.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2019-03-28T15:46:16.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084432/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084432/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084432/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-03-08","Home Office: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many meetings he held with his Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","230045"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084433","Department for International Development","false","2019-03-14","<p>The DFID Chief Scientific Adviser has not met with the Secretary of State during this three month period but did meet once with me.</p><p>The Chief Scientific Adviser continues to provide all Ministers with regular written submissions and briefings on DFID science and research activities.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2019-03-14T17:53:26.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084433/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084433/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084433/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2019-03-08","Department for International Development: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many meetings she held with her Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","230046"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084434","Department for International Trade","false","2019-03-18","<p>My Rt Hon. Friend the Secretary for State and Chief Scientific Adviser met for a one-to-one meeting on 19th December 2019. The Secretary of State and Chief Scientific Adviser also led a delegation of 100 to the annual CES in the USA from the 7<sup>th</sup> to 10<sup>th</sup> of January 2019.</p><p> </p><p>The Chief Scientific Adviser contributes fully to policy development, including through frequent meetings with the Permanent Secretary, Chief Trade Negotiation Adviser and other members of the Department for International Trade’s Executive Committee; as well as engaging more broadly with policy development such as through the Chief Scientific Advisers’ Network.</p>","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart",,"2019-03-18T16:39:13.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084434/answer","Biography information for Graham Stuart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084434/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084434/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2019-03-08","Department for International Trade: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many meetings he held with his Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","230047"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084435","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-03-18","<p>The responsibilities of a Chief Scientific Advisor are performed by the Director of Analysis in the Ministry of Justice. The Director of Analysis attended meetings with the Secretary of State on one occasion between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019.</p>","Charnwood","Edward Argar",,"2019-03-18T16:18:06.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084435/answer","Biography information for Edward Argar","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084435/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084435/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-03-08","Ministry of Justice: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many meetings he held with his Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","230048"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084436","Northern Ireland Office","false","2019-03-14","<p>The Northern Ireland Office does not have a Chief Scientific Adviser.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2019-03-14T14:58:54.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084436/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084436/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084436/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2019-03-08","Northern Ireland Office: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many meetings she held with her Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","230049"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084437","Prime Minister","false","2019-03-15","<p>I have regular meetings with ministerial colleagues, officials and others.</p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2019-03-15T13:13:18.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084437/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084437/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084437/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2019-03-08","Prime Minister: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, how many meetings she held with her Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","230064"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084438","Scotland Office","false","2019-03-14","<p>The Office of the Secretary of State for Scotland does not have its own departmental Chief Scientific Adviser. Ministers of the Department regularly meet with a wide range of officials across Whitehall on a variety of issues.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2019-03-14T11:12:04.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084438/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084438/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084438/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2019-03-08","Scotland Office: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how many meetings he held with his Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","230065"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084439","Department for Transport","false","2019-03-18","<p>The Secretary of State for Transport has had no meetings with the Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019.</p><p> </p><p>As Minister of State, I meet with the Department’s Chief Scientific Advisor regularly and have had multiple meetings with him since December 2018 to discuss topics including the Department’s evidence and analysis strategy, the Future of Mobility Grand Challenge and the Government Office for Science’s Foresight Report on the Future of Mobility.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2019-03-18T10:45:20.963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084439/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084439/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084439/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-03-08","Department for Transport: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many meetings he held with his Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","230066"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084440","Wales Office","false","2019-03-13","<p>The Office of the Secretary of State for Wales does not employ a Chief Scientific Adviser.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Selby and Ainsty","Nigel Adams",,"2019-03-13T15:17:14.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084440/answer","Biography information for Nigel Adams","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084440/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084440/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2019-03-08","Wales Office: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, how many meetings he held with his Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser between 1 December 2018 and 28 February 2019.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","230067"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084441","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-03-13","<p>Government Hospitality organised the Patient Safety Conference reception, hosted by the Secretary of State for Health on behalf of the Department of Health who also paid for the event. Similarly, Protocol Directorate was engaged to organise the St David's Day reception hosted by the First Minister on behalf of the Welsh Government, who also paid for the reception.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2019-03-13T16:30:26.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084441/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084441/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084441/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-03-08","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Official Hospitality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, with reference to the Answer of 7 February 2019 to Question 215122 on Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Official Hospitality, for what purpose his Department organised the (a) Patient Safety Conference Reception and the (b) St David's Day Reception.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","230068"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084442","Cabinet Office","false","2019-03-13","<p>The CSSF has published programme summaries for financial years 2017/18 and 2018/19 on <a href="http://www.gov.uk" target="_blank">gov.uk</a> .</p><p> </p><p>In November 2018, 76 CSSF programme summaries for 2018/19 programmes were published and a further seven programme summaries are due to be published shortly.</p><p> </p><p>The CSSF continues to work towards greater transparency and the programme summaries for 2019/20 will be published later this year.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2019-03-13T09:43:02.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084442/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084442/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084442/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-03-08","Conflict, Stability and Security Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what plans he has for publication of Conflict, Security and Stability Fund programme summaries up to the end of July 2019.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","230069"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084443","Department for Transport","false","2019-03-13","<p>Arriva Rail London (ARL), the train operating company responsible for running the London Overground network under a concession agreement with Transport for London, has proposed to close the ticket offices at 51 London Overground stations in accordance with Schedule 17 of the Ticketing and Settlement Agreement (TSA). Under the TSA process it is for ARL and London TravelWatch to seek to reach agreement on the proposals.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2019-03-13T14:41:53.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084443/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084443/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084443/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-03-08","London Overground: Tickets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 4 March 2019 to Question 226511, whether London Overground has submitted proposals to close ticket offices at any of its stations.","false","Biography information for Kate Hoey","Vauxhall","Kate Hoey","230025"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084444","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-03-14","<p>The 2002 Bali bombings remain fresh in the mind of many in the UK, with the high death toll including 23 British nationals and many other foreign tourists and Indonesians. Following media reports about the possible release of Abu Bakar Ba’asyir, the UK sought urgent clarification from the Indonesian authorities. We understand that the prospect of early release has receded. Our Embassy in Jakarta will continue to monitor developments and to urge the Indonesian government to uphold the rule of law.</p><p>​</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2019-03-14T12:02:00.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084444/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084444/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084444/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-03-08","Abu Bakar Ba'asyir","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations he has made to his counterpart in Indonesia on the proposed early release of Abu Bashir.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","230070"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084445","Department for Education","false","2019-03-15","<p>Ofsted is currently consulting on proposals for a new inspection framework. This includes a separate graded judgement on pupils’ behaviour and attitudes, within which inspectors will consider pupil exclusions. Ofsted has also proposed a new emphasis on examining any use of off-rolling as well formal exclusions. The Department engaged closely with Ofsted as it developed its consultation proposals, and that engagement continues.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2019-03-15T14:24:42.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084445/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084445/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084445/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-03-08","Pupil Exclusions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what recent discussions he has had with Ofsted on how effective management of pupil exclusions can be strengthened in the new inspection framework for schools.","false","Biography information for Bambos Charalambous","Enfield, Southgate","Bambos Charalambous","230098"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084446","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-03-18","<p>​The prevalence of conflict-related sexual violence, including that directed at South Sudan’s displaced population, remains a long standing and serious concern. Most recently, following incidents of widespread rape near Bentiu, including by armed groups, we have repeatedly called for the Government of South Sudan to ensure that these, and all incidents of sexual violence, are fully investigated and perpetrators brought to justice, support provided for survivors, and action taken to prevent such attacks. The UK Defence Secretary visited South Sudan in January 2019, when he discussed our concerns at the highest levels, and urged action to bring an end to sexual and gender-based violence.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2019-03-18T16:27:24.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084446/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084446/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084446/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-03-08","South Sudan: Sexual Offences","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations he has made to his counterpart in South Sudan of sexual violence committed by that country's armed and security forces against displaced persons.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","230071"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084447","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-03-15","<p>We were appalled by the murder of Giulio Regeni in Cairo and we continue to monitor the investigation into his death. As Mr Regeni was an Italian citizen, the Italian Government is taking the lead role on his case. We have consistently raised our concerns with the Egyptian authorities at both Ministerial and official levels, stressing the need for a full and impartial investigation into the circumstances of Mr Regeni's murder. We continue to offer our full support to Italy and urge the Egyptian Government to cooperate fully with the Italian investigators in order to bring Mr Regeni's killers to justice as soon as possible.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2019-03-15T11:41:44.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084447/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084447/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084447/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-03-08","Giulio Regeni","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations he has made to his Egyptian counterpart on their cooperation with the Italian investigation into the murder of former Cambridge University student, Guilio Regeni.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","230072"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084448","Department for Education","false","2019-03-13","<p>There are currently 94 accredited School Resource Management Advisors (SRMAs). SRMAs are not employed directly by the Department and each is signed up to a provider organisation that is responsible for their management and deployment. More can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/esfa-extends-schools-resource-management-adviser-pilot" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/esfa-extends-schools-resource-management-adviser-pilot</a>.</p><p>SRMAs have undertaken or are currently undertaking 221 deployments (130 completed and 91 in progress) to academy trusts, University Technical Colleges (UTCs) and local authorities. Deployments to trusts, local authorities and UTCs have been in the following Education and Skills Funding Agency (ESFA) areas:</p><ul><li>56 to the ESFA North areas (covering the ‘North’ and ‘Lancashire &amp; West Yorkshire’ Regional School Commissioner (RSC) regions);</li><li>48 to the ESFA Central areas (covering ‘West Midlands’ and ‘East Midlands &amp; Humber’ RSC regions);</li><li>42 to the ESFA South Central and East areas (covering ‘NW London and South Central’ and ‘East of England and North East London’ RSC regions); and</li><li>75 to the ESFA South areas. (covering ‘South East and South London’ and ‘South West’ RSC regions).</li></ul><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","230033","2019-03-13T17:40:38.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084448/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084448/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084448/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-03-08","Schools: Cost-effectiveness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many school efficiency advisers have been (a) employed and (b) deployed by his Department since 2017.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","230032"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084449","Department for Education","false","2019-03-13","<p>There are currently 94 accredited School Resource Management Advisors (SRMAs). SRMAs are not employed directly by the Department and each is signed up to a provider organisation that is responsible for their management and deployment. More can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/esfa-extends-schools-resource-management-adviser-pilot" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/esfa-extends-schools-resource-management-adviser-pilot</a>.</p><p>SRMAs have undertaken or are currently undertaking 221 deployments (130 completed and 91 in progress) to academy trusts, University Technical Colleges (UTCs) and local authorities. Deployments to trusts, local authorities and UTCs have been in the following Education and Skills Funding Agency (ESFA) areas:</p><ul><li>56 to the ESFA North areas (covering the ‘North’ and ‘Lancashire &amp; West Yorkshire’ Regional School Commissioner (RSC) regions);</li><li>48 to the ESFA Central areas (covering ‘West Midlands’ and ‘East Midlands &amp; Humber’ RSC regions);</li><li>42 to the ESFA South Central and East areas (covering ‘NW London and South Central’ and ‘East of England and North East London’ RSC regions); and</li><li>75 to the ESFA South areas. (covering ‘South East and South London’ and ‘South West’ RSC regions).</li></ul><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","230032","2019-03-13T17:40:38.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084449/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084449/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084449/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-03-08","Schools: Cost-effectiveness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many school efficiency advisers have been deployed in each region since 2017.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","230033"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084450","Home Office","false","2019-03-13","<p>The Home Secretary and Home Office Ministers conduct visits, and host meetings, on the whole spectrum of Home Office business regularly. It is our policy not to provide details of such visits.</p><p>Information on ministers’ meetings is released quarterly as part of Government transparency and accountability data and is available at: <br><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/home-office-ministerial-gifts-hospitality-travel-and-meetings-july-to-september-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/home-office-ministerial-gifts-hospitality-travel-and-meetings-july-to-september-2018</a></p><p> </p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2019-03-13T14:36:08.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084450/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084450/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084450/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-03-08","Detention Centres","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many times he has visited immigration detention centres since his appointment as Secretary of State for the Home Department; and which immigration detention centres he has so visited.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","230099"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084451","Scotland Office","false","2019-03-14","<p>There is no obligation to publish responses to requests made under the Freedom of Information Act 2000. The Office decided that the cost of updating the published list of responses to Freedom of Information requests since 2014 would not be proportionate to the benefits.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2019-03-14T11:13:00.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084451/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084451/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1084451/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2019-03-08","Scotland Office: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, pursuant to the Answer of 26 April 2018 to Question 136969 on Scotland Office: Freedom of Information, if he will publish the findings of his Department's review of its practices on publication of Freedom of Information responses.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","230100"
