"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083574","Department for International Development","false","2019-03-15","<p>All public government consultations are uploaded onto GOV.UK where one can filter consultations by many criteria, including department, official document status and date of publication.</p><p>a) None are open</p><p>b) A response has been issued to all consultations</p><p>c) Two have been initiated since 2016</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2019-03-15T14:33:31.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083574/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083574/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083574/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2019-03-07","Department for International Development: Public Consultation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many consultations by her Department (a) are open, (b) are closed awaiting a Government response and (c) have been initiated since 2016.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","229744"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083575","Department for International Trade","false","2019-03-13","<p>The Department for International Trade currently has no open consultations.</p><p> </p><p>Four consultations were launched in last year, enabling the public to provide their views on potential future trade agreement negotiations with the USA, Australia, New Zealand, and on the UK potentially seeking accession to join the Comprehensive and Progressive Agreement for Trans-Pacific Partnership. We had over 600,000 responses to the consultations. A government response for each will be published before any formal free trade agreement negotiations commence.</p><p> </p><p>Five consultations have been initiated since 2016, the four in 2018 and a call for evidence in 2017 to identify UK interest in existing UK trade remedy measures.</p>","Meon Valley","George Hollingbery",,"2019-03-13T15:16:47.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083575/answer","Biography information for Sir George Hollingbery","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083575/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083575/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2019-03-07","Department for International Trade: Public Consultation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many consultations by his Department (a) are open, (b) are closed awaiting a Government response and (c) have been initiated since 2016.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","229745"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083576","Department for Transport","false","2019-03-12","<p>The Department for Transport (DfT) currently has 9 consultations open on GOV.UK</p><p> </p><p>There are 30 consultations awaiting a Government response.</p><p>Since 2016, 176 DfT consultations have been published on GOV.UK.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2019-03-12T12:15:36.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083576/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083576/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083576/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-03-07","Department for Transport: Public Consultation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many consultations by his Department (a) are open, (b) are closed awaiting a Government response and (c) have been initiated since 2016.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","229746"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083577","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-03-13","<p>The Department for Work and Pensions has one open consultation, 8 that are closed awaiting a Government response and has initiated 90 consultations since 1 January 2016.</p><p>All public government consultations are uploaded onto GOV.UK where it is possible to filter consultations by many criteria, including department, official document status and date of publication.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2019-03-13T13:25:19.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083577/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083577/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083577/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-03-07","Department for Work and Pensions: Public Consultation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many consultations by her Department (a) are open, (b) are closed awaiting a Government response and (c) have been initiated since 2016.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","229747"
