"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083579","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-03-15","<p>All public government consultations are uploaded onto GOV.UK where they can be filtered by department, status and date. The Foreign Office has published four documents since 2016. For all of these the consultation processes have been concluded. These were: (a) Public consultation on the United Kingdom's future legal framework for imposing and implementing sanctions (2 August 2017) (published jointly with HMT and DIT); (b) Consultation on the UK's Foreign Travel Advice service (25 April 2017); (c) Defence and security innovation: proposed accelerator (11 August 2016) (published jointly with DfT, Home Office, MOD, Dstl, CDE and BEIS); and (d) BIOT Resettlement Policy Review consultation (21 January 2016). There are no consultations pending.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2019-03-15T12:03:41.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083579/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083579/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083579/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-03-07","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Public Consultation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many consultations by his Department (a) are open, (b) are closed awaiting a Government response and (c) have been initiated since 2016.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","229749"
