"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083626","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-03-12","<p>New claims to Employment and Support Allowance (ESA) have now stopped, however claimants can receive the ESA component of Universal Credit (UC). Claimants may also be entitled to New Style ESA which can be claimed alongside Universal Credit if the claimant has paid or been credited with sufficient National Insurance contributions, satisfying the New Style ESA eligibility conditions.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2019-03-12T11:30:36.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083626/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083626/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083626/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-03-07","Universal Credit: Veterans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many veterans in receipt of a war pension are claiming employment support allowance as part of their universal credit claim.","false","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant","229663"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083627","Department for International Trade","false","2019-03-12","<p>None of the Department for International Trade’s suppliers have failed to meet the tax compliance criteria in the Procurement Policy Note 03/14.</p>","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart",,"2019-03-12T10:43:36.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083627/answer","Biography information for Graham Stuart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083627/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083627/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2019-03-07","Department for International Trade: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, with reference to the guidance entitled Procurement policy note 03/14: promoting tax compliance, how many suppliers were allocated contracts by his Department as a result of complying with (a) one and (b) more than one of the mitigating circumstances after failing the tax compliance questions.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","229778"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083628","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-03-12","<p>The Work Capability Assessment is not a condition of entitlement to housing costs within Universal Credit.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2019-03-12T11:43:26.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083628/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083628/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083628/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-03-07","Universal Credit: Veterans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many veterans in receipt of (a) an armed forces compensation scheme guaranteed income payment and (b) the war pension scheme unemployability supplement have undertaken a work capability assessment to prove their entitlement to the housing element of universal credit in each year for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant","229664"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083629","Treasury","false","2019-03-14","<p>The Government is committed to the availability of Islamic finance in the UK to ensure that no one is denied access to competitive financial products for reasons of faith.</p><p>Sharia-compliant home purchase plans are enabled by regulations overseen by the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA). They are currently offered by four UK banks.</p><p> </p><p>Beyond the requirements set out in the FCA regulations, decisions around the pricing and availability of individual mortgage loans remain commercial decisions for lenders, and the Government does not seek to intervene in these decisions.</p><p> </p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2019-03-14T13:31:15.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083629/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083629/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083629/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-03-07","Mortgages: Islam","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many high street banks offer Islamic mortgage services.","false","Biography information for Matthew Pennycook","Greenwich and Woolwich","Matthew Pennycook","229779"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083630","Department for International Trade","false","2019-03-12","<p>I refer [the Honourable Friend for Glasgow North] to the answer I gave to [the Member for Midlothian] on 26 February 2019, UIN 224364.</p>","Meon Valley","George Hollingbery",,"2019-03-12T11:13:33.82Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083630/answer","Biography information for Sir George Hollingbery","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083630/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083630/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2019-03-07","Trade Agreements: NHS","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what his Department’s policy is on the inclusion of private provision of NHS Services in future trade negotiations with other countries in the event that the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","229780"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083631","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-03-12","<p>Thirty-eight per cent of people successfully use GOV.UK Verify to identify themselves. For those who prefer to do this face to face in a Jobcentre that option continues to remain open.</p><p> </p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2019-03-12T16:30:11.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083631/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083631/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083631/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-03-07","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of universal credit claimants have been able to verify their identity successfully online; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","229601"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083632","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-03-12","<p>The information requested is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2019-03-12T16:30:41.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083632/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083632/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083632/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-03-07","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the average time taken is for a universal credit claim to be verified manually when the claimant is not able to verify their identity online.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","229614"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083633","Department for Education","false","2019-03-12","<p>As at 31 January 2019, there were 200 commitments in England entered into the Apprenticeship Service, where the transfer of funds between apprenticeship service accounts has been approved (a commitment is where a potential apprentice, who is expected to go on to start an apprenticeship, has been recorded with the Apprenticeship Service). Of these transferred commitments as at 31 January 2019, there were 130 transferred commitments that had materialised into apprenticeship starts. Further statistics can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/apprenticeship-and-levy-statistics-february-2019" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/apprenticeship-and-levy-statistics-february-2019</a>.</p><p>Information on companies transferring apprenticeship levy funds in each region of England is not available in the format requested. Many levy-paying employers are headquartered in one region but operate across the country meaning that we cannot attribute levy-funds transferred in individual locations. Individual employers have control of the expenditure (and transfer) of apprenticeship levy funds based on their current and future skills needs.</p><p>It should be noted that, from April this year, levy-paying employers can transfer 25% of their levy funds to other employers.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2019-03-12T17:35:43.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083633/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083633/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083633/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-03-07","Apprentices: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many companies in London have transferred support for apprenticeships arising from their apprenticeship levy payments to other employers to date.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","229615"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083634","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-03-15","<p>Applications for a Universal Credit advance can be made in a number of ways: in person, by telephone and also online. To identify and collate the total number of applications made would incur disproportionate cost. Consequently, we do not hold the information requested.</p><p> </p><p>Universal Credit claimants may be eligible for an advance payment, in order to provide extra financial support for those who need it most. The Department has increased the maximum advance a claimant may receive at the start of their claim to 100 per cent of their indicative award and has extended the repayment period to 12 months. From October 2021, this maximum repayment period will be extended further to 16 months.</p><p> </p><p>Around 60% of eligible new claims to Universal Credit received an advance in January 2019. This shows that claimants are being made aware of advances and that our advance system is being utilised so people receive help when they need it.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2019-03-15T15:24:23.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083634/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083634/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083634/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-03-07","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the total number and proportion of universal credit claimants who have applied for advance payments is in each of the past five years; and what number and proportion of such applications have been approved.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","229665"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083635","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-05-22","<p>If a claimant meets the conditions for an advance we aim to make the payment within 72 hours. However, an advance can be paid on the same day the claimant applies if they or their household would suffer genuine hardship if they had to wait 72 hours for the payment.</p><p>Applications for a Universal Credit advance payment can be made in person, by telephone or online depending on the claimant’s circumstances. Depending on the type of advance payment application, we will consider whether the claimant satisfies the eligibility conditions for receiving the advance. If the claimant is eligible we will agree the amount of the advance and the period over which the advance will be recovered from their future Universal Credit payments. The outcome of the application is explained to the claimant and their online journal updated.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2019-05-22T13:37:44.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083635/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083635/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083635/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-03-07","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the process is for her Department when it considers an application for an advance payment for universal credit.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","229666"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083636","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-03-18","<p>If a claimant meets the conditions for an advance we aim to make the payment within 72 hours. However, an advance can be paid on the same day the claimant applies if they or their household would suffer genuine hardship if they had to wait 72 hours for the payment.</p><p>Applications for a Universal Credit advance payment can be made in person, by telephone or online depending on the claimant’s circumstances. Depending on the type of advance payment application, we will consider whether the claimant satisfies the eligibility conditions for receiving the advance. If the claimant is eligible we will agree the amount of the advance and the period over which the advance will be recovered from their future Universal Credit payments. The outcome of the application is explained to the claimant and their online journal updated.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2019-03-18T15:34:04.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083636/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083636/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083636/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-03-07","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how long it takes on average to process an advance payment application for universal credit.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","229667"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083637","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-03-12","<p>None. Pension payments made by the German government are a matter for them.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2019-03-12T15:04:53.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083637/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083637/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083637/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-03-07","Germany: British Nationals Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to his counterpart in the German Government on reports of UK residents who allegedly collaborated with the Nazi regime during the second world war receiving pensions under the war victims' legislation of that country.","false","Biography information for Tommy Sheppard","Edinburgh East","Tommy Sheppard","229781"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083638","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2019-03-12","<p>Corallian Energy Limited submitted an Environment Statement to BEIS’s OPRED team to support an application to drill an offshore appraisal well in Poole Bay. The Environmental Statement, the comments received from statutory consultees and the representations made in response to the public notice were reviewed by the Department and it was concluded that the proposals would not have a significant adverse impact on the receiving environment or the living resources it supports, or on any protected habitats or species or other users of the sea. The decision can be found under Corallian Energy Limited at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/oil-and-gas-environmental-statements-reviewed" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/guidance/oil-and-gas-environmental-statements-reviewed</a></p><p> </p><p>BEIS is extremely aware of the sensitivity of this stretch of the UK coastline, and the area in the immediate vicinity of the drilling location. This was therefore given detailed consideration during the review of the proposals, and appropriate mitigation was included to minimise as far as possible the risk of an accidental spill.</p><p>Officials in OPRED’s Offshore Environmental Inspectorate have visited the rig undertaking the drilling operations in Poole Bay and are content that operations are being undertaken in a responsible manner and in compliance with regulatory requirements.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2019-03-12T11:39:41.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083638/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083638/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083638/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2019-03-07","Oil: Poole Bay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the environmental effect of oil exploration operations in Poole Bay.","false","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","New Forest West","Sir Desmond Swayne","229591"
