"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083661","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-03-13","<p>Section 176 of the Anti-Social Behaviour Crime and Policing Act 2014 inserted into the Magistrates’ Courts Act 1980 a deeming provision (section 22A) whereby shop theft of goods worth £200 or less (‘low-value shoplifting’) is treated as a summary only offence unless the accused elects to be tried by a judge and jury.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2019-03-13T17:33:05.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083661/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083661/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083661/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-03-07","Shoplifting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether offences of shop theft of goods worth £200 or less are classified summary-only crimes since the introduction of the Anti-Social Behaviour, Crime and Policing Act 2014.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","David Hanson","229676"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083662","Home Office","false","2019-03-14","<p>The Home Office collects and publishes data quarterly on police recorded crime, broken down by Police Force Area, which can be found here:</p><p><br><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-recorded-crime-open-data-tables" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-recorded-crime-open-data-tables</a></p><p><br>This includes the number of recorded offences of violence with injury, robbery of business property and fraud. However, information on the value of theft or whether or not fraud was committed online is not held centrally by the Home Office.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","229678 ; 229679 ; 229680 ; 229681","2019-03-14T16:54:25.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083662/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083662/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1083662/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-03-07","Crimes of Violence: Business Premises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many recorded incidences there have been of (a) violence with injury crimes and (b) robberies from business properties in each year since 2012 by police force area.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","David Hanson","229677"
